(40, 22, 9, 23, 55, 1, 3, 'bid to the marriage', 'Invitation to Abundant Provision', 'This connection highlights the invitation to come and partake in a feast, as seen in both passages. Matthew''s call to ''bid to the marriage'' parallels Isaiah''s invitation to ''come ye to the waters,'' emphasizing the accessibility of divine sustenance.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 9, 26, 21, 21, 21, NULL, 'Invitation and Decision Making', 'This connection highlights the theme of choosing a path or direction. In Matthew, the call to ''go ye therefore into the highways'' suggests an invitation to a significant event, while Ezekiel describes the king''s decision-making at ''the parting of the way.''', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 9, 42, 24, 47, 47, 'bid to the marriage', 'Invitation to All Nations', 'This connection highlights the theme of inviting all people to partake in God''s message. Both passages emphasize the call to reach out beyond a specific group, with Matthew focusing on the highways and Luke on all nations.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 10, 46, 6, 9, 11, 'both bad and good', 'Inclusion of the Unrighteous', 'This connection highlights the gathering of both ''bad and good'' in Matthew, paralleling the mention of unrighteous individuals in 1 Corinthians. Both passages emphasize the transformation from a state of unrighteousness to being ''washed'' and ''sanctified.''', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 10, 40, 13, 47, 48, 'gathered together all as many as they found', 'Gathering of Good and Bad', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of individuals, distinguishing between good and bad. In Matthew 22:10, guests are gathered for a wedding, while Matthew 13:47-48 describes a net collecting every kind, sorting the good from the bad.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 10, 47, 12, 21, 21, 'gathered together all as many as they found', 'Invitation and Repentance Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of individuals, highlighting the contrast between those invited and those who have sinned. The call to repentance in 2 Corinthians reflects the need for purity among the guests mentioned in Matthew.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 10, 62, 2, 19, 19, 'both bad and good', 'Connection of Inclusion and Exclusion', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of individuals, with Matthew highlighting the inclusion of ''both bad and good'' and 1 John discussing those who ''went out from us.'' This connection highlights the contrast between those who are accepted and those who reveal their true nature by leaving.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 10, 66, 2, 20, 23, 'both bad and good', 'Invitation and Judgment Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of gathering and judgment. In Matthew, the invitation to the wedding includes both ''bad and good,'' while Revelation warns of judgment against those who follow false teachings, emphasizing the consequences of unfaithfulness.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 10, 66, 7, 9, 9, 'gathered together all as many as they found', 'Gathering of Multitudes', 'This connection highlights the gathering of diverse people in both passages. Matthew emphasizes gathering ''both bad and good,'' while Revelation depicts a multitude ''of all nations, and kindreds, and people, and tongues.''', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 10, 40, 22, 11, 12, 'gathered together all as many as they found', 'Connection of Guests and Garments', 'This connection highlights the importance of being properly prepared for the wedding feast. Both passages emphasize the gathering of guests and the necessity of appropriate attire, as seen in the contrast between those invited and the man without a wedding garment.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 11, 66, 3, 4, 5, 'not on a wedding garment', 'Connection of Garments in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of proper garments. In Matthew, the man without a wedding garment is rejected, while in Revelation, those with unblemished garments are deemed worthy to walk with Christ.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 22, 11, 66, 19, 8, 8, 'wedding garment', 'Wedding Garment and Righteousness', 'This connection highlights the importance of being properly attired for the wedding feast, as seen in both passages. The man without a wedding garment in Matthew contrasts with the saints in Revelation who are arrayed in fine linen, symbolizing righteousness.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
